				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: NEW MELODY COMMAND FOR BARDS!!!<a name="70797"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 9 04 4:15 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Yes.  Singing any other song or /stopsong immediately stops the melody in mid-cast.  It then has to be manually restarted, it won't resume by itself.
<br />

<br />
It also does not recall the last song sung, so if you get to song 3 and theres a fizzle, and start it again, it won't start at song 3 or 4, it starts back at 1.
<br />

<br />
While I do see this as cutting down on repetitive stress injury, it isn't nearly as automated as some are making it out to be.  Especially when they remove the bug that is completely eliminating missed notes.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
